# local.sources.example
# 
# This file shows how to configure local package overrides for development.
# Copy this file to 'local.sources' and modify the paths and commands as needed.
# 
# Format:
# - Non-indented lines are repository paths (absolute or relative to this file)
# - Indented lines are shell commands to build and pack the repository
# - Use {VERSION} placeholder for version and {OUTPUT} for output directory
#
# Examples:

# Local development of a related Aardvark project
/home/dev/aardvark-base
    dotnet tool restore
    dotnet paket restore  
    dotnet build -c Debug src/Aardvark.Base/Aardvark.Base.fsproj
    dotnet paket pack --build-config Debug --version {VERSION} {OUTPUT}

# Another project using relative path
../aardvark-rendering
    dotnet build -c Debug
    dotnet paket pack --build-config Debug --version {VERSION} {OUTPUT}

# Project with specific build requirements
/path/to/custom-project
    ./build.sh
    dotnet pack src/MyProject/MyProject.csproj -c Debug --version-suffix {VERSION} -o {OUTPUT}

# Notes:
# - All packages created this way will override their NuGet/Paket counterparts
# - Caching works best with git repositories
# - Transitive local.sources overrides are supported across repositories
# - Use Debug configuration for faster local development builds
# - The {OUTPUT} directory is managed by Aardvark.Build